Full Title: International Experience and Cooperation in Using IT to Teach
Foreign Languages 
Short Title: IT & FLT 

Date: 23-Oct-2009 - 23-Oct-2009
Location: Moscow, Russia 
Contact Person: Anastasia Atabekova
Meeting Email: atabekoff@gmail.com
Web Site: http://www.fld-rudn.com 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 10-Oct-2009 

Meeting Description:

IT & FLT

Dear Colleagues, 
The Organizing Committee of the Annual Seminar on International Experience and
Cooperation in Using IT to Teach Foreign Languages is pleased and honored to
invite you to take part in the Seminar to be held at Peoples' Friendship
University of Russia, Moscow, on October  23, 2009.

Ways to participate 
- on-line session, 
- on-site participation, 
- publication of abstract/ article in the conference proceedings book (with
ISBN, free of charge, with further sending by post through our university mail
service ) 

Call for Papers

Seminar focus 
The Annual International Seminar will bring together teachers, researchers and 
professionals from all over the world to exchange, discuss and develop their
ideas on the general topic of foreign language teaching and learning in the
digital age. The seminar will offer many opportunities for contact between
various professionals, specialists and practitioners. 

Papers are welcome on the following topic areas: 
Topics of interest include, but are not limited to the following areas: 
- International experience and partnership (USA, Europe, Asia, Russia) in
teaching foreign languages 
- Assessing progress of learning in the digital age 
- IT potential to stimulate and support exploratory learning approaches 
- Cognition in education in the digital age  
- IT in collaborative learning 
- Learning Communities & Web Service Technologies 
- Learning Paradigms in the digital age 
- Student-Centered Learning 
- Technology, learning and expertise 
- IT in teaching LSP

Submissions 
The deadline for  proposals is 10 October 2009. 
The papers should not exceed 8000 units (4 pages  A4 format, Times New Roman,14)
The allowed languages are English, French, Spanish, German. 
Electronic Submissions should be sent in MS Word format to atabekoff@gmail.com





